.TH "NAVIGATION.FORWARD" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Navigation.forward \- Navigation: forward() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]forward()\f[B]\f[R] method of the \f[CR]Navigation\f[R]
interface navigates forwards by one entry in the navigation history.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
forward(options)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]options\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An options object containing the following properties:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]info\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Developer\-defined information to be passed along to the
\f[CR]navigate\f[R] event, made available in
\f[CR]NavigateEvent.info\f[R].
This can be any data type.
You might, for example, wish to display newly\-navigated content with a
different animation depending on how it was navigated to (swipe left,
swipe right, or go home).
A string indicating which animation to use could be passed in as
\f[CR]info\f[R].
.RE
.SS Return value
An object with the following properties:
.TP
\f[B]committed\f[R]
A \f[CR]Promise\f[R] which will fulfill when the visible URL has changed
and a new \f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R] has been created.
.TP
\f[B]finished\f[R]
A \f[CR]Promise\f[R] which will fulfill when all promises returned by
the \f[CR]NavigateEvent.intercept()\f[R] handler are fulfilled.
This is equivalent to the \f[CR]NavigationTransition.finished\f[R]
promise fulfilling, when the \f[CR]navigatesuccess\f[R] event fires.
.PP
Either one of these promises rejects if the navigation has failed for
some reason.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]InvalidStateError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if the \f[CR]Navigation.currentEntry\f[R]\(cqs
\f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry.index\f[R] value is \-1 or
\f[CR]navigation.entries().length \- 1\f[R], i.e., either the current
\f[CR]Document\f[R] is not yet active, or the current history entry is
the last one in the history, meaning that forwards navigation is not
possible, or if the current \f[CR]Document\f[R] is unloading.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]async\f[R] \f[B]function\f[R] backHandler() {
  \f[B]if\f[R] (navigation.canGoBack) {
    \f[B]await\f[R] navigation.back().finished;
    \f[I]// Handle any required clean\-up after\f[R]
    \f[I]// navigation has finished\f[R]
  } \f[B]else\f[R] {
    displayBanner(\(dqYou are on the first page\(dq);
  }
}

\f[B]async\f[R] \f[B]function\f[R] forwardHandler() {
  \f[B]if\f[R] (navigation.canGoForward) {
    \f[B]await\f[R] navigation.forward().finished;
    \f[I]// Handle any required clean\-up after\f[R]
    \f[I]// navigation has finished\f[R]
  } \f[B]else\f[R] {
    displayBanner(\(dqYou are on the last page\(dq);
  }
}
.EE
